A Gucci Designer Earthquake, Goodell=E2=80=99s NFL Fantasy, The
Atlantic=E2=80=99s A.I. War Room
---------------------------------------------------------

Happy Friday, and welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon assortm=
ent of Puck=E2=80=99s
best new reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Matt Belloni digs into the latest obstacles facing the Para=
mount-Skydance merger as F.C.C. boss Brendan Carr opens a public comment do=
cket over the 60 Minutes =E2=80=9Cscandal.=E2=80=9D The Redstone and Elliso=
n families=E2=80=99 Trump ties were supposed to neutralize this very threat=
=2E Now,
both parties are watching the clock as their $8 billion deal faces yet anot=
her delay=E2=80=A6

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: Tara Palmeri sits down with Senator John Fetterman to=
 discuss his beef with Democrats. John Ourand explores Roger Goodell=E2=80=
=99s billion-dollar fantasy of adding an 18th game to the NFL=E2=80=99s reg=
ular season. And in an exclusive Inner Circle
dispatch, Lauren Sherman unearths the drama inside Gucci following creative=
 director Sabato De Sarno=E2=80=99s ouster.

Meanwhile, on the pods: Dylan Byers grills Nick Thompson, C.E.O. of The Atl=
antic, about the inevitable convergence of journalism and A.I. On Fashion P=
eople, Lauren hears from former Harper=E2=80=99s Bazaar editors Cynthia Tru=
e and Dennis Golonka
about their new book on the late, great Liz Tilberis. On Impolitic, John He=
ilemann huddles up with Ezra Klein to dissect Trump=E2=80=99s blizzard of e=
xecutive actions and power grabs. And on The Powers That Be, Eriq Gardner j=
oins Peter Hamby to assess the legal firestorm surrounding the Paramount sa=
le.

